<br>
I find it hard to decide which aim to pursue at the moment: Get AA points? Work on gear upgrades? Hunt for cash? Work on getting epic?<br>
<br>
AA points certainly help the most in everyday playing (SCM, ...).<br>
<br>
Gear upgrades would certainly be nice, this would probably be Thurgadin armor for me for now, and some odd pieces from the bazaar.<br>
<br>
Getting cash might help for getting gear upgrades, as well as saving up for buying an air crown (since I dont think my guild will raid to PoA).<br>
<br>
And the epic is so close, and yet so far away...I guess this will stay random for me, when I get a chance on a piece I will take it.<br>
<br>
I will probably spend the next weeks going for more aa points. This seems to have the greatest benefit to me. What would YOU go for? What is more important for you? Thanks for any replies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
